This place is/was unprofessional to work with. I mistakenly overpaid for my VIP section and still haven't received my money and I was blocked. Everything was unorganized, I had to continuously go to the front entrance to request things that should have already been in place; for example asking for my bottles to be brought out. They gave my friends a hard time entering the place even though they were on my VIP list, which was embarrassing because most of my guests were from out of town. The VIP sections were unkempt and the dress code was definitely not enforced. I felt like I could have came in jeans and sneakers. Nothing like it was displayed online and not worth the money paid. I would not recommend this place at all. I tried to refrain from leaving a bad review, but it has been too much of a disappointment not to speak on it.

This is by far the worst experience. The hours posted are from 10 pm-2 am, when I arrived at 10:15 pm the security team informs us that they are not open yet because the manager is running late? Did you not know it is Saturday night. As I am sitting in line I notice that most of the staff is just arriving to show up for work it is now 10:30 pm. After being let in the place it is barley cleaned and they are very understaffed. It took almost an hour to get our on bottle served to up us in our VIP section if you want to call it that. We had called in a head of time to assure they had Hookah at there lounge; however the Hookah girl did not show up for work that night surprise surprise. I am not the manager but I would just like to inform him/her that there is something called redundancy...please cross train other workers in different areas of your place just in case a scenario like this happens. I mean its not like I am asking them to review my stock portfolio it is just packing a Hookah bowl. So with this assumption if the DJ calls out of work do you close for that night??? If you our going to advertise a upscale lounge and park a Bentley in the front of you establishment please come correct. Enforce your dress code policy's, if you advertise something please have it available. This is nothing less then Hammer Jacks that is now a Lounge.
